cs0x65.parkinglot.command

Class Command<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs0x65.parkinglot.command.Command<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the target class that implements the domain specific commands e.g. ParkingLot

    public class Command<T>
extends Object
    This class represents the domain specific abstraction of the supplied text commands. The class works in co-ordination of the domain specific implementation of Parser like DefaultParserImpl for parking lot domain.

    A typical Command<T> captures all the information required to execute the command on the provided target class indicated by the instance of parameterized type. The information includes:
    • The target T which is the target class implementing the domain specific commands, for e.g ParkingLot along with the arguments.
    • The result object which is the domain specific result of executing the command on the target T
    • The verbMethod Method that will be invoked on the target T to obtain the result
    • Because commands essentially produce formatted output that's rendered on STOUT or STDERR or to file streams/readers, the class also captures the output template and a mechanism to bind values to the template placeholders. Such a processed template is returned for rendering by the corresponding Processor. Additionally, the class provides executeAndPrint() variants that also flushes the output to the provided print stream or writer.

      • getResult

        public Object getResult()
        Returns:
        the domain specific object that's returned by executing the verbMethod on the target. execute and it's variant do the work of generating a formatted textual output that's more suitable for rendering to STOUT or STDERR or to file streams/readers. Make sure to call this method to retrieve the result only after invoking one of the execute method on the current command, failing to do so will return null.

      • setResultAccessors

        public void setResultAccessors(List<String> resultAccessors)
        Parameters:
        resultAccessors - are the accessor/getter method names that are invoked on the underlying target so that the returned values from the invocation are bind to the the output template placeholders. They generate a formatted textual output out of output template that's more suitable for rendering to STOUT or STDERR or to file streams/readers.

      • execute

        public String execute()
               throws CommandOutputFormatException
        Because commands essentially produce formatted output that's rendered on STOUT or STDERR or to file streams/readers, the method prefers to return this output rather than the domain specific result object (which can be retrieved by calling getResult post invocation of this method.
        The method works with the provided output template and result accessors to generate this textual command output. The returned result is ready to be rendered by Processor

        Use executeAndPrint() variants of this method to additionally pass the output to the supplied print stream or writer, in such case Processor can provide such a rendering stream.
        Returns:
        the formatted textual result of the execution of this command that's more suitable for rendering to STOUT or STDERR or to file streams/readers.
        Throws:
        CommandOutputFormatException
